com.sayem.appium.pagefactory.framework.browser.web

Class WebBrowser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sayem.appium.pagefactory.framework.browser.Browser<org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver>
      • com.sayem.appium.pagefactory.framework.browser.web.WebBrowser
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ChromeBrowser, FirefoxBrowser, InternetExplorerBrowser, RemoteBrowser

    public abstract class WebBrowser
extends Browser<org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver>
    Base Browser class. Contains a lot of the configuration that is common across browsers. Subclasses must implement getBrowserType, getDesiredCapabilities, isRemote, and getActions

      • openPageByURL

        public TopLevelPage openPageByURL(java.lang.String href)
                           throws java.net.URISyntaxException
        Opens a new page in the Browser by URL. An absolute URL or the path can be provided. If a path is provided, then the baseTestUrl provided when creating the browser will be used as the base of the URL. Invalidates the cached page and loads a fresh new page.
        Parameters:
        href - - the href from a link, which may be a relative path from baseTestUrl or may be absolute
        Returns:
        - a generic BaseTopLevelPage page object. To open a page with more specific functionality, you must extend BaseTopLevelPage and then call openPageByURL(String, Class).
        Throws:
        java.net.URISyntaxException

      • openPageByURL

                                         throws java.net.URISyntaxException
        Opens a new page in the Browser by URL. An absolute URL or the path can be provided. Invalidates the cached page and loads a fresh new page.
        Parameters:
        href - - the href from a link, which may be a relative path from baseTestUrl or may be absolute
        pageClass - - the TopLevelPage class to load.

        java.net.URISyntaxException
